Privacy Policy for GPT Code Saver

Effective Date: 19.9.24

1. Introduction
We respect your privacy and are committed to protecting any personal information that you may share with us. This Privacy Policy outlines how GPT Code Saver ("the extension") collects, uses, and protects your information.

2. Information We Collect
GPT Code Saver does not collect, store, or share any personal data. The extension solely interacts with the active tab to save code snippets as local files. No user activity, personal information, or browsing history is transmitted or stored.

3. Permissions Explanation
The following permissions are required to provide the core functionality of the extension:

activeTab: Allows the extension to access the currently active tab (ChatGPT) in order to enable saving of code snippets.
scripting: Used to inject scripts into the page to add "Save Code" buttons next to code blocks.
downloads: Enables the extension to save code snippets as files to your local device.
4. Host Permissions
The extension requires access to the domain https://chatgpt.com/* to identify and interact with code snippets generated by ChatGPT. This permission is used solely for the purpose of allowing users to save these snippets locally.

5. No Remote Code or Data Transmission
GPT Code Saver does not execute or retrieve remote code from external servers. Additionally, the extension does not transmit any data to external servers. All actions, such as saving code snippets, are performed locally on your device.

6. Security
We take the security of your information seriously. Although the extension does not collect or transmit personal data, it is designed to ensure the safety and security of your browsing experience.

7. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We reserve the right to modify this Privacy Policy at any time. If changes are made, we will update the effective date at the top of this document.

8. Contact Information
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at nivmuroch@gmail.com.
